Aboitiz Power, Daelim, Foster’s, HTC, Nan Ya: Asia Ex-Japan Equity Preview

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-05-01T22:07:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-01/aboitiz-power-daelim-foster-s-htc-nan-ya-asia-ex-japan-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes today in Asian trading, excluding  Japan .
Stock symbols are in parentheses, and share prices are from the
previous close, unless noted otherwise.  Aboitiz Power Corp. (AP)  : The company is ready to invest
in a 300-megawatt coal-fired power plant in the southern
Philippine island of Mindanao, a stock-exchange filing showed.
The company is prepared to spend its own funds to accelerate the
construction of the project, it said. The stock gained 1.8
percent to 31.55 pesos.  China Airlines Ltd. (2610)  (2610 TT): The airline reported a
first-quarter loss of NT$379 million ($13.3 million) compared
with a profit NT$2.56 billion a year earlier, a Taiwan stock-
exchange filing showed. The stock fell 0.8 percent to NT$18.3.  Daelim Industrial Co. (000210 KS): Daelim said ONGL Petro
Additions Ltd. of  India  canceled a contract to build a high-
density polyethyelene plant. The two companies were unable to
narrow differences on terms before the final signing of the
agreement, the Seoul-based company said in a regulatory filing.
The stock fell 1.2 percent to 121,000 won.  Formosa Petrochemical Corp. (6505)  (6505 TT): Taiwan’s only
publicly traded oil refiner reported first-quarter net income of
NT$17.9 billion compared with NT$11 billion a year earlier, the
company said in a stock-exchange filing. The stock gained 1
percent to NT$100.50.  Foster’s Group Ltd. (FGL)  :  Australia ’s biggest brewer
said its consensus earnings before interest, tax and SGARA for
the 2011 fiscal year is in a range of between A$1.01 billion
($1.1 billion) and A$1.1 billion for the combined beer and wine
businesses. The stock fell 2.3 percent to A$5.62.  HTC Corp. (2498)  (2498 TT): The Taiwanese smartphone maker expects
second-quarter revenue of around NT$120 billion and shipments of
about 11 million to 11.5 million units, the Taoyuan, Taiwan-
based company said in a statement. The stock was unchanged at
NT$1,300.  Hyundai Engineering & Construction Co. (000720 KS): South
Korea’s largest builder that was taken over by Hyundai Motor
Group said net income in the first quarter dropped 9.6 percent
to 92.2 billion won. Sales fell 3.1 percent to 1.95 trillion won.
The stock increased 2.4 percent to 89,900 won.  MacroAsia Corp. (MAC)  : Lufthansa Technik Philippines
Inc., a provider of aircraft maintenance and repair services
that’s 49 percent owned by the company, will spend $30 million
to expand its facility, a stock-exchange filing showed. The
stock fell 1.9 percent to 3.05 pesos.  Nan Ya Plastics Corp. (1303)  (1303 TT): The world’s largest
processor of plastics for pipes and imitation leather reported
first-quarter net income of NT$13.4 billion compared with NT$9
billion a year earlier, a stock exchange filing showed. The
stock fell 0.3 percent to NT$87.80.  To contact the reporter on this story:
